{
  "texts": [
    "Consequently, their \"Design Intuition\" could not be processed into \"Artefact Knowledge\" capable of reflecting garment construction principles and technical features.",
    "Although Gen AI provided its contribution for \"Discovery\" in the conceptualisation and research phase, \"Inspiration\" for the stimulation of divergent and convergent thinking, and \"Visualisation\" for the presentation of design proposals and their refinement, a gap was highlighted in the selected Gen AI tools related to sector-specific expertise.",
    "Indeed, the \"Design Development\" and \"Digital Pattern Making & Virtual Prototyping\" phases required the technical intervention of the fashion design students to translate the generated material into viable design solutions.",
    "However, it should be considered how some experimental tools are attempting to cover this gap (Kularatne et al., 2019; Guo et al., 2023).",
    "A further conclusion that emerged was that the design complexity expressed by Gianfranco Ferré's principles of \"Form,\" \"Human Body,\" and \"Material\" (Ferré and Frisa, 2009) could not be interpreted and codified by Gen AI, further underlining their inability to encode structures, volumes and geometries enclosed in the garment construction."
  ]
}